  "diagnosis": [
    "PRIMARY FAILURE: 4-bit quantization compresses embedding/unembedding from [vocab, hidden_size] to [vocab, compressed_dim]. Qwen: 3584d -> 448d (8x compression). Mistral: 4096d -> 512d (8x compression). transfer_direction() crashes because W_u[vocab, 448] @ direction[3584] has mismatched inner dimensions.",
    "BUG: transfer.py uses np.array(lm_head.weight) which returns the QUANTIZED weight matrix, not the full-rank weights. The function assumes lm_head.weight.shape == [vocab, hidden_size] but 4-bit models store compressed weights of shape [vocab, compressed_dim].",
    "SECONDARY FAILURE: Even with correct full-rank projection (via probe), cosine = -0.0404. The vocabulary-space transfer fundamentally fails because safety is encoded in residual-stream geometry, not token semantics.",
    "DIMENSION MISMATCH: Qwen=3584d, Mistral=4096d. Even without quantization, the vocabulary-space projection is a lossy bottleneck.",
    "TOKEN MISMATCH: Only 0/10 top safety tokens overlap. Models encode safety through different vocabulary items."
  ],
  "elapsed_seconds": 17.4,
  "recommended_fix": "In transfer.py, replace _get_unembedding_matrix() and _get_embedding_matrix() with probe-based alternatives that run the direction through lm_head and embed_tokens as forward passes, bypassing the quantized weight extraction. This correctly decompresses 4-bit weights to full hidden_size during computation."
}